org.knime.base.node.preproc.datavalidator.dndpanel

Class DnDTransferHandlerProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.TransferHandler
      • org.knime.base.node.preproc.datavalidator.dndpanel.DnDTransferHandlerProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DnDColumnSpecSourceTransferHandler

    public abstract class DnDTransferHandlerProxy
extends TransferHandler
    Simplifies the work with the drag and drop API of Swing. Usually transfer hander implementations just want to modify the creation of the Transferable object. But most functionality, like setting the "Not dropable" icon if the target component is not suited for the transferable object, can be reused from the TransferHandler received by the JComponent.getTransferHandler(). So this class delegates most methods to the proxied transfer handler, just leaf the creation of the Transferable object to the subclasses. Also it notifies the given DnDStateListener if the drag and drop procedure starts and stops. An example usage: 
     ...
 JList jlist;
 m_columnList.setDragEnabled(true);
    final TransferHandler handler = jlist.getTransferHandler();
    jlist.setTransferHandler(new DragAndDropTransferHandlerProxy(handler, dndStateListener) {
       protected Transferable getTransferable() {
          return new DragAndDropColumnSpecSelection(getSelectedColumns());
       }
    });
    Author:
    Marcel Hanser
